<br>
If you buy a dsl router, just make sure it supports DHCP and the standard the dsl people are using... most routers support both &quot;standards&quot; now (mine does), but knowing which they are using before hand can't hurt.<br>
<br>
PS I'm using a Netgear RT311 and haven't had a single problem with it, and after putting in my information it's been happily pulling DHCP addresses for about 8 months now without a hitch. <p><hr align="center" width="80%" size="2">
