<br>
Not sure about the specifics you're dealing with Uriel, but if my past experience with ISDN is any indication, you should use whatever equipment the telco is using.  For ISDN this was neccessary because of all kinds of weirdness and incompatibilities between PPP implementations.  For DSL, I'd recommend it because if you need support, the folks at the telco will be familiar with the gear.<br>
<br>
Some folks I respect speak well of the Linksys DSL router, BTW, so if the telco has no reccommendation you might look at one of those.<br>
<br>
